Sentencas: In the present work, we have developed a multilayer tape casting and co-sintering process to fabricate large area anode-supported electrolyte film, which is critical for planar type reduced temperature solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: A study of multilayer tape casting method for anode-supported planar type solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs)

Sentencas: Nickel/yttria-stabilized zirconia (Ni/YSZ), nickel/scandia-stabilized zirconia (Ni/ScSZ) cermets, ScSZ, Ce(0.8)Gd(0.2)d(1.9) (CGO), and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF)-CGO were used as materials of anode substrate, anode functional layer, electrolyte, interlayer and cathode, respectively.
Titulo: A study of multilayer tape casting method for anode-supported planar type solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs)

Sentencas: The powders of these functional layers were ball milled with organic additives to form slurries, which were assembled together with the multilayer tape casting procedure to get the green tapes.
Titulo: A study of multilayer tape casting method for anode-supported planar type solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs)

Sentencas: After dryness, the green tape was co-sintered at 1400 degrees C for 4 h in air to get the large area anode-supported electrolyte film (thickness similar to 15 mu m).
Titulo: A study of multilayer tape casting method for anode-supported planar type solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs)

Sentencas: For cells preparation, LSCF-CGO composite cathode was deposited by screen-printing method and sintered at 1100 degrees C for 3 h. The area-specific resistance (ASR) of the obtained single cell was found to be similar to 0.99 Omega cm(2) at 850 degrees C with H-2/O-2 as the operating gases, and the maximum power density achieved similar to 0.63 W cm(-2).
Titulo: A study of multilayer tape casting method for anode-supported planar type solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs)

Sentencas: The thickness of the (Zr,Ce)O-2-based solid solution formed at the ScSZ/CGO interface during high temperature sintering was investigated.
Titulo: A study of multilayer tape casting method for anode-supported planar type solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs)

Sentencas: The results illustrate that fabrication of anode-supported electrolyte film for planar SOFCs with a CGO interlayer is possible by multilayer tape casting procedure, which is both cost-effective and feasible.
Titulo: A study of multilayer tape casting method for anode-supported planar type solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs)
